      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, the resource is the invocation, but in the name it\u0027s being treated as a resource (in the general AIP sense) rather than an invocation. Another way to put it is, why /do/ we need this name? Why /aren\u0027t/ we using the invocation ID? The reason for that is because AIP dictates *resources* be named according to this scheme.\n\nI don\u0027t want to bikeshed over this, and I think the last suggestion is a superset of the information we\u0027ve mentioned wanting to include, so the last suggestion sounds fine to me.",
